page.title: 01HYTHE ROAD, FELTWELL
page.content: This block is cut into two by the cut off channel, which runs along the Eastern boundary of the Fens. To the East lies the higher ground made up of rolling chalk hills leading towards Breckland. Along this runs the road from Feltwell to Methwold Hythe. The Northernmost edge of the village of Feltwell appears in this block. West of the Cut Off Channel the land is barely above sea level and comprises peat soil, drained by numerous dykes. Apart from the edge of Feltwell Village the only inhabitants of the block live at a farm on the Southery Road, which runs through the South Western corner of the block.
